1. Executive Summary
DocuMind AI is a browser-native, AI-powered document intelligence layer that activates automatically when users open any document — PDFs, DOCX, PPTX, TXT, WPS, EPUB, and more — directly in their browser or via a companion web app. It eliminates the need to manually read through lengthy documents by instantly summarizing content and enabling natural-language querying against the document corpus.

Users can ask questions like " What are the key obligations in Section 4?" or "Summarize the financial projections for Q3" and receive precise, cited answers — without ever scrolling through the document manually.

🎯 Vision: Target outcome: Reduce average document review time by 70%, enabling professionals to extract critical insights in seconds rather than hours.

2. Problem Statement
2.1 The Core Pain
Modern knowledge workers spend 30–40% of their working day reading and parsing documents — contracts, research papers, reports, policy manuals, meeting notes — much of it repetitive or irrelevant to their specific need. This results in:
•Wasted hours reading documents to find one specific clause or data point
•Missed insights buried deep in lengthy or complex files
•Bottlenecks in decision-making because the right information is hard to surface quickly
•Cognitive overload managing multiple document formats across different tools

2.2 Existing Solutions Fall Short
Current tools are inadequate:
