6. Feature Requirements
6.1 Core Features (MVP)
F-01: Auto Document Detection
When a user opens a supported document in their browser (e.g., navigates to a PDF URL or opens a .docx via Google Drive/OneDrive preview), the extension automatically detects the document type and renders a floating sidebar assistant.
•Auto-detection triggers on: PDF MIME type, document file extensions in URL, embedded viewers (Google Docs, Office 365 Online)
•Sidebar appears within 1 second of document load
•Manual trigger available via extension icon for any tab

F-02: Instant Document Summarization
On detection (or user request), the system generates a tiered summary:
•Executive Summary (3–5 sentences): The most critical takeaways
•Section-by-Section Breakdown: Hierarchical summary matching the document structure
•Key Entities Panel: People, dates, amounts, organizations, clauses auto-extracted and displayed as chips
•Summary is generated within 3 seconds for documents up to 50 pages

⚠️ Critical: Summaries must include inline citations (e.g., 'As stated on Page 4, Section 2.3...') to maintain auditability — a critical requirement for legal and compliance use cases.

F-03: Conversational Q&A (RAG Engine)
Users can ask free-form questions in natural language. The system retrieves relevant document chunks and generates grounded, cited answers.
•Uses Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) with semantic vector search over chunked document text
•Every answer includes a source citation linking to the exact page/section
•Multi-turn conversation: follow-up questions maintain context of prior turns
•Fallback behavior: if the answer is not in the document, the system explicitly states so rather than hallucinating

F-04: Multi-Document Corpus (Web App)
In the web app, users can build a personal document library:
•Drag-and-drop upload of multiple files
•Organize documents into Projects/Folders
•Cross-document Q&A: 'Across all contracts in my folder, which ones expire in 2026?'
•Persistent vector store per user — documents remain indexed across sessions

F-05: Export & Share
•Export generated summaries as .PDF, .DOCX, or Markdown
•Copy any answer to clipboard with one click
•Share a summary link (web app only) with optional password protection

6.2 Enhanced Features (Post-MVP)
F-06: Smart Annotations
Users can highlight passages in the document and the assistant will:
•Explain the highlighted text in plain language
•Translate it to another language (30+ languages supported via the LLM)
•Suggest alternative phrasings or flag ambiguous legal language

F-07: Comparative Analysis
Upload two versions of a document (e.g., Contract v1 vs Contract v2) and receive:
•Diff summary: what changed, what was added, what was removed
•Risk delta: new risks introduced in the newer version

F-08: Document Q&A Voice Mode
•Users can speak questions via microphone (Web Speech API)
•Answers are read aloud via text-to-speech
•Useful for accessibility and hands-free workflows

F-09: Smart Table & Chart Extraction
•Automatically detects tables within PDFs/DOCX and renders them as interactive grids
•Charts in PPT/PDF are described in text; underlying data is extracted if available
•Data can be exported to .CSV or opened in a mini spreadsheet view

