7. Technical Architecture
7.1 System Components — 100% Free Stack
Free Stack: All tools below are free and open-source unless marked [Free Tier]. No paid subscriptions are required to build and launch the MVP.

Component	Free Technology	Notes
Chrome Extension (Frontend)	React + TypeScript + Manifest V3	100% free — open web standards
Document Parser	PyMuPDF, python-docx, python-pptx, Tesseract OCR	All open-source, pip install
Chunking + Embeddings	LangChain OSS + nomic-embed-text or all-MiniLM-L6-v2	Runs locally, zero API cost
Vector Store	ChromaDB (dev) then Qdrant self-hosted (prod)	Both fully open-source
LLM (Local)	Ollama + Mistral 7B / LLaMA 3 / Gemma 2	Runs on your machine, completely free
LLM (Free API fallback)	Google Gemini 1.5 Flash [Free Tier] or Groq API [Free Tier]	Gemini: 1M tokens/day free; Groq: LLaMA 3 + Mistral
Backend API	FastAPI (Python) on Railway.app or Render.com [Free Tier]	No credit card needed for free tier
Web App Frontend	Next.js 14 + Tailwind CSS on Vercel [Free Tier]	Vercel free tier is generous for indie projects
Auth	Supabase Auth [Free Tier] or NextAuth.js self-hosted	Supabase: 50,000 MAU free
Database	Supabase PostgreSQL [Free Tier] or Neon.tech [Free Tier]	Both fully managed, zero ops
File Storage	Supabase Storage [Free: 1GB] or Cloudflare R2 [Free: 10GB]	R2 has no egress fees — better long-term
LLM Observability	Langfuse OSS self-hosted on Railway	Core product is open-source
Infra Monitoring	Grafana + Prometheus (self-hosted)	Industry-standard, fully open-source
Semantic Query Cache	Redis OSS (self-hosted) or Upstash Redis [Free Tier]	Cuts redundant LLM calls significantly

Limits: Free tier ceilings: Supabase (500MB DB, 1GB storage, 50K MAU), Vercel (100GB bandwidth/month), Railway (500 hrs/month). Sufficient for MVP + early user validation.

