13. Open Questions & Decisions Needed
5.Client-side vs. server-side processing: For highly sensitive enterprise users, should we build a local processing mode (e.g., integrate with Ollama running locally)? This would eliminate data leaving the device. Recommended: yes — Ollama is already in the stack, so a 'local mode' toggle is low effort.
6.Embedding model selection: nomic-embed-text (higher quality, needs more RAM) vs. all-MiniLM-L6-v2 (lighter, faster) — run an eval on a sample corpus to pick the right default for target hardware.
7.Gemini vs. Groq as the free API fallback: Gemini 1.5 Flash has higher context window (1M tokens); Groq is faster (250 tokens/sec). Decision: use Groq for chat Q&A (speed matters), Gemini for full-document summarization (context window matters).
8.Offline support: Should the Chrome Extension cache summaries and allow re-querying offline? Requires local vector store (IndexedDB + WASM-based embedding model like transformers.js).
9.INR pricing for Indian market: Given the student and SMB target segment in India, consider offering a lower-priced INR tier (~Rs 299/month for Pro) to drive adoption in the home market first.

