14.2 Glossary
•RAG: Retrieval-Augmented Generation — relevant document chunks are fetched and injected into an LLM prompt to generate grounded, cited answers
•Vector Embedding: A numerical representation of text capturing semantic meaning, enabling similarity-based search
•Chunking: Splitting a document into overlapping segments of fixed token length for efficient retrieval
•Semantic Cache: Stores prior LLM query results and retrieves them for semantically similar (not just identical) future queries — reduces API calls
•Ollama: Open-source tool for running LLMs locally on your own machine — completely free, no API key needed
•ChromaDB: Open-source vector database that runs embedded in Python — ideal for development and small-scale production
•Qdrant: Open-source vector database with a self-hosted server mode — better performance at scale than Chroma
•Sentence Transformers: Python library for generating text embeddings locally using models like all-MiniLM-L6-v2 — no API cost
•MV3: Chrome Manifest Version 3 — the current extension platform with stricter security and performance rules
•RLS: Row-Level Security — a Postgres/Supabase feature ensuring users can only access their own rows in the database

